{"id": "duc04-testb-15:18#54", "contents": "Wyoming has been one of the nation's holdouts in passing hate crimes legislation, rejecting three bills since 1994. However, following the death of Matthew Shepard, Governor Jim Geringer appealed to lawmakers to reconsider their opposition. Geringer met with Shepard's father, Dennis, who expressed that his son's death should not be used to \"further an agenda\" and that any new legislation should be carefully considered to avoid taking away the rights of others."}
